Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced) (whole onion for 4). Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered). Halve @potato buns{2}.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} (spread across entire sheet for 4 servings) with a drizzle of oil, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step), @salt, and @pepper.

Roast on top rack for ~{12%minutes}. (You'll add more to the sheet then.)

While potatoes roast, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels. Season with half the @celery salt{1%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings), half the @dried thyme{1%teaspoon} (you'll use more later), remaining Fry Seasoning, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in chicken for pork. Cook until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side. (Skip roasting chicken.)

Once potatoes have roasted 12 minutes, remove from oven. Carefully place chicken on empty side of same baking sheet. Roast on top rack until chicken is cooked through and potatoes are browned and tender, ~{8-10%minutes} more. (For 4, leave potatoes roasting; add chicken to a second #baking sheet{} and roast on middle rack.)

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add sliced onion; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in a drizzle of oil, @flour{1%tablespoon}, and remaining thyme. Cook, stirring, until mixture is lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Whisk in @water{1/2%cup} (1 cup for 4), @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and @sugar{1/4%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4). Bring to a simmer; cook, whisking constantly, until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> Use pan used for chicken here.

Turn off heat; season with @salt and @pepper to taste.

While onion cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, @pesto{1%tablespoon} (or more to taste), and juice from one lemon wedge (juice from two wedges for 4 servings).

Toast buns directly on top rack of oven until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Toss potatoes with lemon zest.

Spread a thin layer of creamy pesto sauce onto cut sides of buns. Fill buns with chicken and saucy onion.

Divide sandwiches and potatoes between plates. Serve with remaining lemon wedges and remaining creamy pesto sauce on the side for dipping.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.